<note class="clinical-tip" id="note-00001">
<title>Ask Open-ended Questions</title>
<para id="para-00008">Nurses should always ask clients open-ended questions to elicit a more informative history. For example, the nurse could ask “How often do you eat red meat each month?” instead of “Do you eat red meat?”.</para>
</note>
